sights.name: Old city bridge
sights.quote: Historic bridge featuring red portals & scenic views of the river & quaint, colorful houses.

sights.name: Nidaros Cathedral
sights.quote: Soaring, gothic cathedral dating to 11th century, plus Bishop's palace with a crown jewels exhibit.

sights.name: Kristiansten Festning
sights.quote: Built 1681–1685, this fortress overlooking the city offers a museum, guided tours & a seasonal cafe.

sights.name: Trøndelag Folk Museum
sights.quote: More than 80 buildings, some dating from 12th century, in open-air, cultural heritage museum.

sights.name: Archbishop's Palace, Trondheim
sights.quote: Archaeological artifacts & re-enactments showcased in a 13th-century stone castle with a courtyard.

sights.name: Tyholttårnet
sights.quote: Radio tower standing 124 meters tall with a scenic observation deck & rotating restaurant.

sights.name: Ringve Music Museum
sights.quote: Music history museum featuring a global collection of instruments at an 18th-century farm.

sights.name: Vitensenteret i Trondheim
sights.quote: Educational science center with interactive exhibits & regular organised kids' activities.

sights.name: National Museum of Decorative Arts
sights.quote: Museum featuring Norwegian & international decorative & industrial artwork, plus rotating exhibits.

sights.name: Rockheim
sights.quote: Museum on Norwegian popular music featuring a hall of fame, interactive exhibits & a media library.

sights.name: NTNU Vitenskapsmuseet
sights.quote: Exhibits recreating medieval Trondheim, Norwegian nature & environment, plus ecclesiastical art.

sights.name: Trondheim Maritime Museum
sights.quote: Quaint maritime history museum featuring model boats, photos & memorabilia, plus a kids’ play area.

sights.name: Stiftsgården
sights.quote: Elegant Baroque townhouse that passed into the possession of the Norwegian royal family in 1906.

sights.name: The Emigrant Monument - Leiv Eiriksson Statue
sights.orig_name: The Emigrant Monument - Leiv Eiriksson Statue

sights.name: Munkholmen
sights.quote: Islet off Trondheim, site of a former monastery, fort & prison, with a restaurant open in summer.
